[It initially may seem confusing but this is a buck in Grant County [items 1 and 2 above], which is outside of the surveillance zone.

The doe is inside Racine County [item 3 above], but was within the surveillance zone as a perimeter county.

Certainly Grant County represents and expansion of territory of this disease and a case can be made for the fact that Racine County is a technical expansion as well.

Both of these cases will certainly cause an increase in the borders of the surveillance zone.

The state of Wisconsin can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at http://healthmap.org/r/4vl5. A Wisconsin county map can be seen at http://www.digital-topo-maps.com/county-map/wisconsin.shtml. - Mod.TG]
